entries.femaleVariant: <kiroshi l="creo" o="Sa ki santi?" t="What is that stink?" b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Ah. De kadav k ap mache. Youn te leve soti nan tonm nan, lòt la ap chèche li." t="Ah. Two walking corpses. One has risen from the grave, while the other seeks it." b="" a=""/>
Your spooky shit don't impress anyone, Slider.
Fuck me… Solomon Reed. I would be lying if I said I have missed you.
Now cut the shit and do us the courtesy of hearin' us out.
We need a good 'runner.
Heard of the SF1 crash?
No love lost 'tween you two, huh?
Need some intel. Street says you're the one to get it.
Plane crash in Dogtown – heard about it?
No love lost 'tween the two of you, eh?
entries.maleVariant: No love lost 'tween you two, huh?

entries.femaleVariant: Me? Heh. I am a blind man. I see no'hing, know not'ing. Cyberspace is my only field of vision.
Bastards! You murder my people in cold blood…
<mothertongue l="creo" m="Donk dim sa." b="" a=" What, specifically, do you want from me?"/>
"Plane?" Hah. You mean de Space Force One. Everyone hear 'bout dat.
Need your help locatin' someone who was on board.
And I would surely oblige were I not blind, wheelchair-bound, and did not give zero fucks about dat or you.
C'mon, stop pretendin' like you got a choice.
Dose who speak to Reed have a strange habit of vanishing or committing suicide.
Lookin' for a woman I lost contact with.
Not even gonna try bargainin'?
Just like that? No hagglin'?
Got a malfunctioning Relic in my skull. 'S how she made contact. That help any?
Soon after SF1 crashed, a 'runner was attacked while on the Net. Attack severed our link. Need to locate her, stat.
Ah, so you want one to investigate Net traffic on de day of de crash.
Hmm... Perhaps. I will need a peek at dis trinket in your head.
I already know de score.
It is dis or not'ing – you choose.
[Sit and jack in] Watch him close, Reed.
Ugh, keep your eyes on 'im, Reed.
[Sit and jack in] Don't like this one bit.
Jacked into a Voodoo Boy's system once. Sprung a nasty surprise on me.
Dis was who? Perhaps I know him.
Brigitte's attack hound – Placide.
<mothertongue l="creo" m="fwenk" b="Dat strutting " a="? I would say he not play fair."/>
You would say correctly.
I stop dealing wid de fanatics outside de wall a long time ago.
<mothertongue l="creo" m="Tankou yon doktè." b="Not to worry. My tech is clean, precise. " a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Fout !" t="Fuck!" b="" a=""/>
I see... traces. Bursts of data in cyberspace, the wake of someone's passage.
You out of your minds coming to me wid dis shit!
What're you talkin' about?
Think he means you, Johnny.
Think Slider just happened on you hangin' out in my head.
Nah, this is somethin' else.
What'd you see?
De Blackwall. It bring only death.
De woman – did you know she use de Blackwall protocol to connect wid you?
Specifics, Slider.
Can't say I did.
Why am I not surprised…?
Had no idea, no.
Nope. Can't say I'm surprised, though.
How to explain to layman... De Net has layers, various vectors for translocation.
Now you do.
What's that mean for us? For what we need?
<mothertongue l="creo" m="E fout." b="" a=" Do you know what it is you bring me?"/>
Enlighten us.
Think you're overreactin', choom.
You do not understand.
Non-negotiable, Slider. We need to find her.
<mothertongue l="creo" m="Mèd..." b="" a=" It's my lucky day."/>
What the...!?
[Confirm data transfer] Let’s go...
Argh! That's a skull cracker. Just what the doc ordered. Thanks.
Songbird – thought we lost you... What happened?
entries.maleVariant: Songbird – thought we lost you, what happened?

entries.femaleVariant: We got disconnected.
Never mentioned using the Blackwall.
So, whenever we linked up, talked... didn’t mention you were tappin' into the Blackwall…
I didn’t. You didn’t need to know that.
That thing… It almost fried my brain. I had to look for help... beyond the Blackwall.
Not exactly. That's clear.
Songbird! Are you OK?
Everything OK?
What's going on?
Slider! What's going on?
Was glad to see you here.
Confirmed she's using the Blackwall…
Looked tired, ailing.
Seemed glad that you and I've teamed up.
She's tapped into the Blackwall, didn't deny it – no big thing, kinda.
She looked sick, almost like… like our link was hurting her.
entries.maleVariant: She looked sick, almost like… our link was hurting her.

entries.femaleVariant: Song needs our help, Reed. Hansen's nabbed her, holdin' 'er for… reasons.
Black Sapphire – said Hansen’s throwin' a big bash there. We get in, she'll find us. Any idea what and where this Sapphire is?
We can't just barge in. Doubt we have anyone on the inside or affiliated who could crack open a door, either…
<mothertongue l="creo" m="Putain de mèd !" b="" a=" Dis I do not believe…"/>
You can be de chief of de NCPD, a corpo CEO or even de fucking president herself…
You are out of your mind.
Besides, as long as she's out there, they catch her scent, they catch yours now, too. They'll sic their wirehead freaks onto you and your people.
So you'll help me clean this up, cover all tracks, snip any threads leading back to you and consequently – us.
V? How...?
Heard it ain't exactly... safe.
Workin' together now. With Alex, too.
Listen, V. Don't have much time. Hansen's people tracked me down after I rezzed the Chimera. I've been... detained.
I'm not in any danger. Not as long as I behave, do what I'm told. I need your help…
There's... Something's not right, girl.
Argh…! Fucking Blackwall...
Black Sapphire, V. Hansen's hosting a huge shindig there. Crash it on the sly. I'll find you. Make sure to tell Reed.
Argh aargh!
Fuck!
Think Slider's dead.
Poor bastard...
Think… Slider might be dead…
Poor bastard…
It's over. He short-circed.
What did Songbird tell you?
Connection severed…
Slider… He flatlined 'cause of us.
He was a murderer. He killed two innocent local 'runners. I have zero sympathy for this piece of shit.
Need you to come clean. Were you gonna off him no matter what?
Question's moot. Slider's dead, what's done is done.
So, Songbird, what's up with her?
But since you are partners, you must know dat by now. Speak your piece.
Are you all right, V?
[Jack out]
Is everything all right?
Let us see what we 'ave here…
Come on, let's delta outta here. There could be more of Slider's lackeys lurkin' around.
Let's move on, find a quiet corner…
Well, just so happens what we need is one who knows cyberspace, sees lots in it.
Heard about me? Huh. How?
Me, my temple – we are one. My eyes and ears are everywhere.
This isn't a temple, it's a malicious daemon mill. And you're no priest, you're a two-bit bandit and murderer.
Murderer, eh? It takes one to know one.
If one party is backed into a corner, it is not negotiation, it is extortion.
You say tomato, I say fucking deal with it, Slider.
Don't know you yet.
Dunno. Don't know you yet, Slider.
I am called many t'ings. Wilky Laguerre, de Blind Fury of de Cyberspace, a t'orn in de NUSA's fat ass. Take your pick.
You forgot to add “double-murderer and all-around coward.”
Here to negotiate.
Heard about me?
Here to make a deal, nothin' more.
A deal? Let me guess…
An empty promise and a bullet to de brain when you decide I am of no use to you – dat kind of deal?
I am all ears.
De Langley man send a clear message.
Well, now you're part of this madness, too. Welcome to the shitshow.
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Modi…!" t="Goddamn it…!" b="" a=""/>
[Stand] Our fault he's dead.
Looks like he couldn't handle the load.
[Stand] Wasn't that good after all.
C'mon, V... Really thought he'd leave 'im breathin'? With everything the gonk knew?
Looks that way.
Your G-man's a cold-blooded pragmatist. Was never gonna let Slider live.
Good. It means she trusts you. Anything else?
We need to find her, fast. Did she drop any coordinates?
Surprised? Why? Take Slider – how the Wall sent him up, huh?
That’s the Black Sapphire. A would-be hotel that ended up a failed multi-billion eddie investment... Hansen's fortress smack in the middle of Dogtown.
They made their choice when they opened up on us.
I knew poor souls who try to strike a deal wit' Solomon Reed. Remember dem, Agent Reed?
We're here to negotiate, Slider. Cut a deal.
Ever done this before?
Flatlined, period.
That all you got to say?
That all you got to say?
Planned to kill him anyway, didn't you…
You don't fuckin' say?
God dammit… I can't imagine any worse news than that.
Take it easy, Slider.
Do that and we'll be square. You'll be off the FIA's hook, too.
You're part of this insanity now, too.
Jack him out, Reed!
Jack him out, Reed!
Unplug Slider! Now!
And you holo if you snag any solid intel.
[Open]
Ever done anything like this before?
What? Be de bridge between hosts using de Blackwall protocol? What de fuck do you think, eh?!
De woman – she is walking, ticking bomb, megatons. She go boom… everybody fucked in de ass. Every last one.
<mothertongue l="creo" m="Miray nwa a." b="" a=" It is a dam dat protects us, de civilized world, from de strange <Rich color=\"MainColors.ActiveBlue\">bèts</> of de cyber wilderness."/>
Think you're exaggerating.
Blackwall’s why you fell out with the Pacifica Voodoo Boys?
<mothertongue l="creo" m="ravèt" b="To de AIs past de Blackwall, you are no more dan a cockroach, a " a=". A fragment of outdated code with no meaning."/>
That why you an' the Pacifica Voodoos don't see eye to eye? 'Cause they're pokin' holes in the Blackwall?
Dey do not penetrate, only jerk off next to it. NetWatch try to keep dem in check.
Is that... Sol Reed? How…? Ah, right, Myers…
I can hardly believe he's here, but... it's a good thing.
But dere is one t'ing dat must not be touched – de Blackwall.
If your two-leg bomb crack de dam down de middle, it will unleash a flood, wipe us off de map just like Haiti…
Dis why NetWatch flatline any who put integrity of Blackwall at risk. Dis no laughing matter, my friend. It is a concern for de safety of all.
<mothertongue l="creo" m="gigit" b="But you 'ave to be cracked in de first place to want to stick your " a=" into a live-wire outlet…"/>
Confirm de data transfer before I change my mind.
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Sak pase la." t="What the hell went down here?" b="" a=""/>
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Mouri tankou poul nan yon dimanch, tout... Sèvè a tou!  Dechire..." t="Dead as chickens on a Sunday, all... And the server! Fucked…" b="" a=""/>

<kiroshi l="creo" o="Nou chache, tout kote, konprann? Apre, dyab yo ki te fè sa, nou peye yo tounen nan plon, klè!?" t="We search, everywhere, get it? And the devils who did this, we pay them back in lead, clear?" b="" a=""/>
You will not.
Whatever.
Nah, no chance, Slider.
Well… OK, I guess.
I will be gentle. Dis I promise.
I can't see. Are we waiting for someone or just scratching our balls?
Risky as shit, that.
I’m putting my life on the line, not yours.
And I haven't for a sec forgotten what we agre--
Got the link back up, we spoke. She's fine, mostly… Needs our help, but she's fine, in one piece.
All right. Gimme the detes later.
Here we go...
Over there. See the taller of the two scrapers, next to the one with a big-ass screen?
That's why you, my friend, need to restore V's connection to our girl.
Heard what he said about messin' with the Blackwall, right? Risky business.
Sounds fuckin' dangerous.
It's even riskier to let Songbird poke more holes in it. We need to make contact with her. Communication's key.
Perhaps you do. I do not.
See it?
Blackwall-to-Relic was the only way to reach you after SF1 was hacked.
And you? You brought death to Maman Brigitte. Will that be your gift for me as well?
And you? You put Maman Brigitte under your spell. Will you bewitch me as well?
So? What will it be? Will you put me down like you did dat bitch Brigitte?
So? What will it be? Will you strike a bargain wit' me as you did wit’ dat bitch Brigitte?
Alex and I'll pull some strings, run our contacts... You do the same, you know... think of who you know around here. Maybe we’ll happen on an idea, find a way.
Know a local fixer... goes by Mr. Hands. Could ring him.
Do it. We’ ll be in touch.
I am blind, not deaf.
Time to delta, V. Just 'cause we got in without dropping bodies doesn't mean they'll wave us goodbye.
Bon voyage, Slider.
That explains a lot.
Fuck... Explains a lot, actually.
Means we're fucked.
Rogue AIs will drown the Net. And all of us with it.
Black Sapphire – said Hansen’s throwin' a big bash there. We get in, she'll find us.
